               <head>Masnavis of ʿAṭṭār, 5 items (a-e)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129656 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100085">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection of mystically-inspired mas̲navīs and a treatise by or traditionally ascribed to the great Sufi master and poet, ʿAṭṭār, comprised of two fragments: 1) items a-d, apparently compiled and transcribed by a certain 
            <persName key="person_f8293" role="scr">Shaykh Bāsiṭ the munshīʾ</persName>; 2) item e, extracted from an earlier manuscript. Volume not dated; datable to 1650-1750. Shikastah āmīz; transcription attributed at the beginning to Shaykh Bāsiṭ the munshīʾ; scribal nastaʿlīq Stamped foliation. Lacking original binding. Paper dust wrapper (BEIC legal publication). Folios unbound; wormholes, stains, creases. Condition poor.
                  </summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian, Arabic</textLang>
